## ❀ Code-Based Evidence ────୨ৎ────────୨ৎ────

The code became an important part of the engineering process because earlier versions were too long and created behavior conflicts. Simplifying the code helped make Cheese easier to debug, tune, and explain.

| Code Area | What It Controls | Why It Matters |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **PID centering** | Keeps Cheese between the walls during straight movement. | Supports stable navigation and reduces drifting. |
| **Wall protection** | Reacts when the robot gets too close to a wall. | Helps prevent collisions. |
| **Curve logic** | Controls how Cheese enters and exits curves. | Helps the robot complete corners more consistently. |
| **Color detection** | Reads floor markings. | Supports curve timing and lap/corner logic. |
| **Parking logic** | Controls the final stop behavior. | Helps Cheese finish in the correct area. |
| **HuskyLens bridge** | Supports obstacle recognition through Arduino. | Allows the robot to use camera-based information for red and green obstacles. |
| **Lighting support** | Improves sensor visibility. | Helps both HuskyLens obstacle recognition and color sensor floor detection. |

